            . I am a <rs id="t18090111-61-viclabel365" type="occupation">broker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090111-61-victim629 t18090111-61-viclabel365"></join> at <placeName id="t18090111-61-crimeloc366">No. 24, Smith's buildings, Battle bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18090111-61-crimeloc366" type="placeName" value="No. 24, Smith's buildings, Battle bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18090111-61-crimeloc366" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090111-61-off363 t18090111-61-crimeloc366"></join>; I only know I missed the carpeting from the front of the shop; when I came home I was informed the prisoner was detected.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18090111-61-person631">
                  JOSEPH 
                  KEY
               <interp inst="t18090111-61-person631" type="surname" value="KEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18090111-61-person631" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18090111-61-person631" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live five doors from the prosecutor's. On the 13th of December, about a quarter before five in the evening, from information I watched two lads that were walking backwards and forwards at Mr. Chalkley's shop.</p>
               <p>Q. Was the prisoner one of these two lads - A. Yes; I saw the prisoner step into Mr. Chalkley's shop and take a piece of carpeting; I seized hold of him about five or six yards from the place where he first laid hold of it; the other ran away; I asked him what he was going to do with the carpetting; he said he was only going to look at it; he dropped it down when I laid hold of him; I picked it up and took him back to the shop.</p>
               <p>The property produced and identified.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going to see a young man, a smith, at Islington; when he laid hold of me there was no one with me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18090111-61-verdict367" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18090111-61-verdict367" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 18.</p>
